                            <comment id="12893196" author="cmale" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 15:00:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is possible to set Random in the SessionIDManager programmatically using the following code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Server server = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Server();
HashSessionIdManager idManager = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; HashSessionIdManager();
idManager.setRandom(&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Random());
server.setSessionIdManager(idManager);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893198" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 15:05:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;here is a patch (not for committing) to see if it resolves it. if so i think we should do this from tests...&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893199" author="mikemccand" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 15:12:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That patch works for me!!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893200" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 15:14:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;seems slightly hackish, but is it ok to check a sysprop in JettySolrRunner to enable this?&lt;br/&gt;
we could then set it from ant for tests and be done with it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893207" author="rcmuir" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 15:20:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch that checks sysprop, set from &apos;ant test&apos;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893210" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 15:27:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I see no problem in havin an insecure hash generator for session ids. When tests are running, the jetty is localhost only and never in production. So in my opinion, the first patch without sysprops is perfectly fine. There is nothing insecure in it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893211" author="markrmiller@gmail.com" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 15:30:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That jetty runner is not a test class.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893224" author="mikemccand" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 16:03:09 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;patch that checks sysprop, set from &apos;ant test&apos;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch works for me too!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think this is a good approach (set a system prop)... +1 to commit.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12893226" author="thetaphi" created="Wed, 28 Jul 2010 16:08:38 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;That jetty runner is not a test class. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ah there are two of them.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12894395" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Sun, 1 Aug 2010 16:30:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This solves some of the test failures I&apos;ve been seeing.  +1 to commit!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
